<subSubSection id="CEE065083552FFE6FF1FFDDFFBC0FBEE" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="864536833552FFE6FF1FFDDFFD45FC72" blockId="60.[151,1437,529,1060]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B48EEA913552FFE6FF1FFDDFFECDFDE6" bold="true" box="[151,269,530,556]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Remarks:</emphasis>
The Madagascan race of the Eurasian Moorhen 
<taxonomicName id="41FA4D003552FFE6FCA4FDDFFB13FDE6" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[812,1235,529,556]" class="Aves" family="Rallidae" genus="Gallinula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloropus">
<emphasis id="B48EEA913552FFE6FCA4FDDFFBCDFDE6" box="[812,1037,530,556]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Gallinula chloropus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FB94FDDFFB0BFDE6" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1052,1227,529,556]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref49504" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. 10 th Ed., vol. 1. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae (Stockholm), 823 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is found throughout 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FF4BFDFBFE8AFD9A" box="[195,330,566,592]" name="Madagascar" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and on the 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FE5AFDFBFD48FD9A" box="[466,648,566,592]" name="Comoros" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Comoro Islands</collectingCountry>
, and is also a resident breeder on 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FB82FDFBFBB7FD9A" box="[1034,1143,566,592]" name="Mauritius" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FB38FDFBFACFFD9A" box="[1200,1295,566,592]" name="RÃ©union" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">RÃ©union</collectingCountry>
(A. 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FACCFDFBFF1FFDBE" author="Newton, A." pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="18 - 19" refId="ref51878" refString="Newton, A. (1861 a) Description of a new species of water-hen (Gallinula) from the island of Mauritius. Proceedings of the Scientific Meetings of the Zoological Society, 1, 18 - 19." type="journal article" year="1861">Newton 1861a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FF63FD97FE1EFDBE" author="Cheke, A. S. &amp; Hume, J. P." box="[235,478,602,628]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref43343" refString="Cheke, A. S. &amp; Hume, J. P. (2008) Lost Land of the Dodo: an Ecological History of Mauritius, Reunion &amp; Rodrigues. T. &amp; A. D. Poyser, London, 464 pp. [reprinted 2011]" type="book" year="2008">Cheke &amp; Hume 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FE62FD97FCCAFDBE" author="Safford, R. J. &amp; Hawkins, A. F. A." box="[490,778,602,628]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref54791" refString="Safford, R. J. &amp; Hawkins, A. F. A. (2013) The birds of Africa. Volume VIII. The Malagasy Region. Christopher Helm, London, 1024 pp." type="book" year="2013">Safford &amp; Hawkins 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="594188213552FFE6FCC7FD97FC71FDBE" box="[847,945,602,628]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B48EEA913552FFE6FC50FD97FB60FDBE" box="[984,1184,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="41FA4D003552FFE6FB9DFD97FB60FDBE" authorityName="Newton" authorityYear="1861" box="[1045,1184,602,628]" class="Aves" family="Rallidae" genus="Gallinula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyrrhorrhoa">pyrrhorrhoa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was collected in 1861 on 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FF35FDB3FEEDFD52" box="[189,301,638,664]" name="Mauritius" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, when Alfred Newton received the skin from his brother, Edward (A. 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FBE9FDB3FACBFD52" author="Newton, A." box="[1121,1291,638,664]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="18 - 19" refId="ref51878" refString="Newton, A. (1861 a) Description of a new species of water-hen (Gallinula) from the island of Mauritius. Proceedings of the Scientific Meetings of the Zoological Society, 1, 18 - 19." type="journal article" year="1861">Newton 1861a</bibRefCitation>
, b). Another specimen had been previously been collected in 1831 (
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FD75FD6FFC79FD76" author="Desjardins, J." box="[765,953,674,700]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="45" refId="ref44211" refString="Desjardins, J. (1831) Abstract of the Proceedings of the &quot; Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Isle Maurice, &quot; to the 24 th of August 1830. Proceedings of the Committee of the Science and Correspondence of the Zoological Society of London, 1, 45." type="journal article" year="1831">Desjardins 1831</bibRefCitation>
), at the same time that the eggs were probably recorded (
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FEC9FD0BFE77FD2A" author="Cari, P." box="[321,439,710,736]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="121 - 128" refId="ref42849" refString="Cari, P. (1904) Observations sur quelques oiseaux de l'Ile Maurice. Ornis, 12, 121 - 128." type="journal article" year="1904">Cari 1904</bibRefCitation>
). Cossigny (Charpentier de 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FD7CFD0BFC5DFD2A" author="Cossigny, J. F." box="[756,925,710,736]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 608" refId="ref42984" refString="Charpentier [de] Cossigny, J. F. (1799) Voyage a Canton, capitale de la province de ce nom, a la Chine: par Goree, le Cap de Bonne esperance et les iles de France et de la Reunion. Andre, Paris, i-viii + 1 - 608." type="book chapter" year="1799">Cossigny 1799</bibRefCitation>
) first observed them on 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FB3CFD0BFAE1FD2A" box="[1204,1313,710,736]" name="Mauritius" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
during the 1790s, and it appears that they were by then well established (
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FCC6FD27FB84FCCE" author="Cheke, A. S. &amp; Hume, J. P." box="[846,1092,746,772]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref43343" refString="Cheke, A. S. &amp; Hume, J. P. (2008) Lost Land of the Dodo: an Ecological History of Mauritius, Reunion &amp; Rodrigues. T. &amp; A. D. Poyser, London, 464 pp. [reprinted 2011]" type="book" year="2008">Cheke &amp; Hume 2008</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FBDFFD27FB38FCCE" author="Michel, C." box="[1111,1272,746,772]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref50558" refString="Michel, C. (1992) Birds of Mauritius. 3 rd Edition. Editions de l'Ocean Indien, Stanley, Rose Hill, Mauritius, 46 pp." type="book" year="1992">Michel (1992)</bibRefCitation>
thought that it had been introduced by the French, but provides no evidence to support this claim and it appears unlikely. It was also first observed on 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FE03FCFFFE2AFC86" box="[395,490,818,844]" name="RÃ©union" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">RÃ©union</collectingCountry>
in 1831 and was also considered common there at that time (
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FB04FCFFFAEAFC86" author="Sganzin" box="[1164,1322,818,844]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref55649" refString="Sganzin, 1840) Notes sur les mammiferes et sur l'ornithologie de l'ile de Madagascar. Memoires de le Societe du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle de Strasbourg, 3 (1), 1 - 49." type="journal article" year="1840">Sganzin 1840</bibRefCitation>
). The lack of records from the 17th century, plus its absence from the fossil-rich Mare aux Songes deposits, suggests that 
<emphasis id="B48EEA913552FFE6FA09FC9BFEFEFC5E" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="41FA4D003552FFE6FF3BFCB7FEFEFC5E" authorityName="Newton" authorityYear="1861" box="[179,318,890,916]" class="Aves" family="Rallidae" genus="Gallinula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyrrhorrhoa">pyrrhorrhoa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a recent colonist that may well have populated the niche of 
<taxonomicName id="41FA4D003552FFE6FB80FCB7FB79FC5E" authorityName=": Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[1032,1209,890,916]" class="Aves" family="Rallidae" genus="Fulica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="newtonii">
<emphasis id="B48EEA913552FFE6FB80FCB7FB79FC5E" box="[1032,1209,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fulica newtonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after it had become extinct (
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FF7AFC53FE25FC72" author="Cheke, A. S. &amp; Hume, J. P." box="[242,485,926,952]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref43343" refString="Cheke, A. S. &amp; Hume, J. P. (2008) Lost Land of the Dodo: an Ecological History of Mauritius, Reunion &amp; Rodrigues. T. &amp; A. D. Poyser, London, 464 pp. [reprinted 2011]" type="book" year="2008">Cheke &amp; Hume 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FE79FC53FDBAFC72" author="Hume, J. P." box="[497,634,926,952]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="195 - 237" refId="ref48084" refString="Hume, J. P. (2013) A synopsis of the pre-human avifauna of the Mascarene Islands. In: Gohlich, U. B. &amp; Kroh, A. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 8 th International Meeting of the Society of Avian Paleontology and Evolution. Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien, pp. 195 - 237." type="book chapter" year="2013">Hume 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="864536833552FFE6FF46FC0FFBC0FBEE" blockId="60.[151,1437,529,1060]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
The Madagascan Moorhen occurs in most remaining wetland areas of 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FC6DFC0FFB92FC16" box="[997,1106,962,988]" name="Mauritius" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
today, especially in the north where it is abundant (pers. obs) (
<figureCitation id="1EC12A063552FFE6FD81FC2BFD9DFBCA" box="[521,605,998,1024]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1081,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,1081,1916]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 38. The last surviving Mascarene rail, Madagascan Moorhen Gallinula chloropus pyrrhorrhoa (centre on rock), at the coastal Anse la Raie wetlands on the northern tip of Mauritius. This was once the habitat of Fulica newtonii. Photograph by the author." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335563/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
), and is well established on the Ã‰tang St. Paul and other wetland areas up to an altitude of 
<quantity id="41029B663552FFE6FEC7FBC7FE6BFBEE" box="[335,427,1034,1060]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="1000.0">1,000 m</quantity>
on 
<collectingCountry id="FEED76133552FFE6FE5DFBC7FDF4FBEE" box="[469,564,1034,1060]" name="RÃ©union" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">RÃ©union</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FDCAFBC7FD0AFBEE" author="Milon, P." box="[578,714,1033,1060]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="129 - 178" refId="ref50626" refString="Milon, P. (1951) Notes sur l'avifaune actuelle de I'ile de la Reunion. Terre Vie, 98, 129 - 178." type="journal article" year="1951">Milon 1951</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E26B4B723552FFE6FD5EFBC7FC35FBEE" author="Safford, R. J. &amp; Hawkins, A. F. A." box="[726,1013,1034,1060]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref54791" refString="Safford, R. J. &amp; Hawkins, A. F. A. (2013) The birds of Africa. Volume VIII. The Malagasy Region. Christopher Helm, London, 1024 pp." type="book" year="2013">Safford &amp; Hawkins 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
